The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, April 20: Air India will offer low fares on select domestic routes to attract passengers in the summer rush. The Apex (advance purchase excursion) fares, to be introduced in 35 domestic sectors, can be as low as Rs 2,494 one way if booked 20 days in advance and Rs 2,694 if bought 10 days before travel.                             
	 New Delhi, April 20: The Foreign Investment Promotion Board (FIPB) today cleared Yamahas proposal to transfer its Indian sales from Yamaha Motor India Sales Ltd to a new entity  India Yamaha Motor. The proposal was deferred earlier as it was felt that the move would lead to retail trading.                             
	 New Delhi, April 20: Commodity market regulator Forward Markets Commission is monitoring sugar futures and will take regulatory steps, if required, to avoid further rise in prices, a senior official said. The market regulator is also monitoring the price movement of potato and rubber.                            
	 New Delhi, April 20: Reliance Industries, which last week surrendered its export-oriented status for one of its two refineries for domestic fuel sales, is set to reopen its petrol pumps, which were shut a year ago.                             
	 Mumbai, April 20: Two nominees of Danone on Britannia Industries board have resigned, days after the Wadia group and the French food giant ended their joint venture agreement.                             
	 New Delhi, April 20: Tata Teleservices will invest $2 billion to roll out GSM mobile services in the country in the next few weeks, beginning with south India and then moving to the east.                            
	 New York, April 20: Pepsico has offered to buy out two of its largest bottling firms  Pepsi Bottling Group and PepsiAmericas  for about $6 billion. Pepsico would be offering $29.50 per share for Pepsi Bottling Group and $23.27 apiece for PepsiAmericas.                                                                                                                           
